## Image Guidelines

### Format Requirements
- **Primary format**: WebP for modern browsers
- **Fallback format**: JPG/PNG only if absolutely required
- **Optimization**: All images should be compressed and optimized

### Responsive Images
Use the following naming convention:
- `image-name-small.webp` - Mobile (up to 480px)
- `image-name-medium.webp` - Tablet (481px - 767px)  
- `image-name-large.webp` - Desktop (768px+)

### Example Usage in HTML:
```html
<picture>
  <source srcset="img/hero-large.webp" media="(min-width: 768px)">
  <source srcset="img/hero-medium.webp" media="(min-width: 480px)">
  <img src="img/hero-small.webp" alt="Description" class="img-fluid" loading="lazy">
</picture>
```

### SEO Requirements
- All images must have meaningful `alt` attributes
- Use descriptive filenames (avoid generic names like "image1.webp")
- Include width and height attributes when possible for CLS prevention

### Performance
- Use `loading="lazy"` for images below the fold
- Use `loading="eager"` for above-the-fold images
- Consider using `srcset` and `sizes` for responsive images